ProtoResult:
. "A sequence $\{\mathbf{X}_r\}$ in $\R^n$ converges if and 
   only if for each $\epsilon>0$ there is an integer $K$ such 
   that $$ |\mathbf{X}_r-\mathbf{X}_s|<\epsilon r,s\ge K. $$"
